(firstQuint)Influence of Anesthesia Technique on Postoperative Evolution After Urogenital Surgical Interventions.

 The study investigates the effect of combined anesthesia on occurrence of acute kidney injury in robot assisted laparoscopic urogenital surgery.

Renal function is assessed according to the new RIFLE and AKIN criteria, and by determining serum and urinary neutrophil gelatinase associated lipocalin.

